<paragraph id="0C0736939F43FF834CF5590A7CCDFF66" blockId="6.[151,1440,152,2018]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1440,152,218]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824D0F590A7A7BFADD" box="[317,565,1352,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824D0F590A7A7BFADD" box="[317,565,1352,1377]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Phaelota kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824F76590A7CB3FADE" authority="Prathapan and Viraktamath" authorityName="Prathapan and Viraktamath" box="[836,1277,1352,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacobyi">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824F76590A7BF9FADD" box="[836,951,1352,1377]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P.jacobyi</emphasis>
Prathapan and Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
by its excarinate anterofrontal ridge (anterofrontal ridge with a vertical carina medially in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF82481F59327CEEFA35" box="[1069,1184,1392,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacobyi">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF82481F59327CEEFA35" box="[1069,1184,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. jacobyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and extremely short spermathecal duct (spermathecal duct nearly twice as long as receptacle in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF82482F59DA7CDFFA0D" box="[1053,1169,1432,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacobyi">
P. 
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF82480959DA7CDFFA0D" box="[1083,1169,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">jacobyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The antebasal transverse impression is laterally well impressed and strongly punctate in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824FF459827C74FA65" box="[966,1082,1472,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacobyi">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824FF459827C74FA65" box="[966,1082,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. jacobyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while it is imperceptible in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF8249B459827950F9BD" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8249B459827950F9BD" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The general color as well as elytral spots are also different in these two species. 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF82493E59AA7998F996" authority="Prathapan and Viraktamath" authorityName="Prathapan and Viraktamath" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindhoori">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF82493E59AA7DD2F9BD" box="[1292,1436,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. sindhoori</emphasis>
Prathapan and Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824E6B5A527AB3F995" box="[601,765,1552,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824E6B5A527AB3F995" box="[601,765,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a short spermathecal duct, but they can be easily separated by the chocolate brown color and black spots on the elytron in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF8248075A7A7C95F9ED" box="[1077,1243,1592,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8248075A7A7C95F9ED" box="[1077,1243,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF8248DD5A7A7D30F9ED" box="[1263,1406,1592,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindhoori">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8248DD5A7A7D30F9ED" box="[1263,1406,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. sindhoori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is entirely brownish red except eyes and 5 
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824E455A1D7ACBF9C5" bold="true" box="[631,645,1631,1657]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
7 distal antennomeres piceous, 
<figureCitation id="94832A169F43FF824FCF5A227CC9F9C6" box="[1021,1159,1631,1658]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="19.[151,269,1957,1981]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,184,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-45@19.[246,1344,179,1935]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Phaelota sindhoori. 59 – dorsal habitus, 60 – head, 61 – metafemur, 62 – pronotum, 63 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs 59 
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8248655A1D7C28F9C5" bold="true" box="[1111,1126,1631,1657]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
62
</figureCitation>
). The receptacle of the spermatheca in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824D625ACA7993F91D" box="[336,477,1672,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindhoori">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824D625ACA7993F91D" box="[336,477,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. sindhoori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is subequal to the pump with a concave outer side (receptacle shorter than pump with either sides convex in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824DD35AF27AC8F975" box="[481,646,1712,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824DD35AF27AC8F975" box="[481,646,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824E925AF27CCFF976" authority="Prathapan and Viraktamath" authorityName="Prathapan and Viraktamath" box="[672,1153,1712,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaishakha">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824E925AF27B7BF975" box="[672,821,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. vaishakha</emphasis>
Prathapan and Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
can be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824CEF5A9A79C8F94D" box="[221,390,1752,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824CEF5A9A79C8F94D" box="[221,390,1752,1777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: transverse, highly convex antennal callus (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F43FF82493A5A9A7DDDF94E" box="[1288,1427,1751,1778]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–69" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[219,1374,198,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-51@20.[213,1378,197,2059]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 64–69. Phaelota vaishakha. 64 – dorsal habitus, 65 – pronotum, 66 – head, 67 – lateral habitus, 68 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views, 69 – spermatheca." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs 64 
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8249545A957D3BF94D" bold="true" box="[1382,1397,1751,1777]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
69
</figureCitation>
) (antennal callus oblique, longer than wide and moderately convex in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824FDA5B427CC1F8A5" box="[1000,1167,1792,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824FDA5B427CC1F8A5" box="[1000,1167,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); antebasal transverse impression distinct (antebasal transverse impression nearly imperceptible in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF8248255B6A7CF5F8FD" box="[1047,1211,1832,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8248255B6A7CF5F8FD" box="[1047,1211,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and lateral pronotal margin strongly curved (lateral pronotal margin weakly curved in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824F895B127C10F8D5" box="[955,1118,1872,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824F895B127C10F8D5" box="[955,1118,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF8248445B127D5CF8D5" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[1142,1298,1872,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8248445B127CCAF8D5" box="[1142,1156,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8248A05B127D5CF8D5" box="[1170,1298,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824D035B3A7995F82D" box="[305,475,1912,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824D035B3A7995F82D" box="[305,475,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by transverse antennal callus and distinct antebasal transverse impression. 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF8249B45B3A7950F805" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF8249B45B3A7DDBF82D" box="[1414,1429,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824CA55BE27950F805" box="[151,286,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824D8F5BE27A7DF805" box="[445,563,1952,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauliki" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824D8F5BE27A7DF805" box="[445,563,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. mauliki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824E0E5BDD7ACEF805" bold="true" box="[572,640,1951,1977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="25FF57FA9F43FF824E0E5BDD7ACEF805" box="[572,640,1951,1977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
but can be separated by its excarinate anterofrontal ridge (anterofrontal ridge is with a vertical carina medially in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F43FF824EFA5B8A7B72F85D" box="[712,828,1992,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauliki">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F43FF824EFA5B8A7B72F85D" box="[712,828,1992,2017]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P.mauliki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the shape of the spermatheca which has a convex outer side (outer side of spermatheca concave in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F42FF834F2C5CDA7BDBFF0D" box="[798,917,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauliki">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F42FF834F2C5CDA7BDBFF0D" box="[798,917,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. mauliki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Though the color is highly variable in 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F42FF8349B45CDA78A1FF65" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauliki">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F42FF8349B45CDA78A1FF65" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. mauliki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it lacks black spots on elytron (
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F42FF834E5E5C827B41FF65" box="[620,783,192,217]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kottigehara">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F42FF834E5E5C827B41FF65" box="[620,783,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. kottigehara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has black spots on the elytron).
</paragraph>
